The Revolutionary Government of Zanzibar has issued a new travel advisory aiming at controlling global COVID-19 pandemic. The document which becomes effective from April 1, 2022 has been signed by Minister for Health, Mr Nassor Ahmed Mazrui. Tanzanians, returning residents and members of the crew are required to truthfully fill in an online Travellers Health Surveillance Form within 24 hours before arrival to Tanzania through Zanzibar Those travellers entering Zanzibar including Tanzanians, returning residents and those in transit through land borders who are fully vaccinated will be exempted from RT-PCR, Antigen Rapid Test or edge scan requirement regardless of the flights taken Unvaccinated travellers will be required to present a negative Covid-19 RT-PCR or NAATs certificates with QR Code obtained within 72 hours before departure. The document stated that, travellers arriving from the United Arab Emirates (UAE) who did not meet the aforementioned will be tested using the Exponential Deep Examination (EDE) scan upon their arrival. “If found positive they will be tested with Rapid PCR test at an additional cost of 110 USD at Abeid Amani Karume International Airport (AAKIA), allowed to self-isolate and the results will be sent via email or any other means,” it added. On the other hand, those who are not fully vaccinated and have no negative Covid 19 RT-PCR certificates will be dealt as follows; in case  of air transport and International marine vessels will be tested for Covid-19 using RT-PCR test at their own cost of 100 USD in Zanzibar and the result will be delivered to them while self-isolated. In case of inland vessels, travelers will be tested using Rapid Antigen Test at their own cost of 25 USD followed by RT-PCR for confirmation for positive cases at a cost of 80 USD. Under the new advisory, children aged 5 years and below, crew and transit will be exempted from both RT PCR and Rapid Antigen Test requirements. The document stressed on the need for all AAKIA departing travellers through Fly Dubai, Etihad or Emirates who wish to take a conventional PCR test conducted 24-48 hours prior to departure a fee of 80 USD will be payable online via Zanzibar Covid-19 testing system.